About  





































 













 





Sojitz Corporation of America (SCA)




Sojitz Corporation of America (SCA) is the U.S. subsidiary of Sojitz Corporation, an integrated global trading company with $35 billion in annual trade transactions. Headquartered in Tokyo, Sojitz has 88 offices, 396 subsidiaries, and 14, 330 employees around the world.  For over 100 years (see full history), SCA has done business with trust, reliability, and results, characteristics that are synonymous with the Sojitz name.
Main business activities include:

International trade (export, import, offshore, domestic and counter-trade)
Marketing and distribution
International project management
Trade financing and project financing
Transportation, insurance, and customs services
Natural resource development
Direct investment, debt financing, leasing, and asset-based financing

Through 9 business divisions SCA has the ability to operate across an enormous scope of industries and sectors and to work with thousands of companies (giants like Boeing and Nike) in the Americas  and around the world.
Within the Aerospace & IT division of SCA is the Satcom department focusing on the satellite communications industry with concentration in the maritime, government, oil/gas, utilities, and commercial/enterprise market. The Satcom team has over 40 years of experience in satellite communications with unparalleled customer support.








New Japan Radio Co. (NJRC)
For over 50 years, New Japan Radio Co. is the world class manufacturer of Block Up Converters and Low Noise Blockers for the Satellite Communications industry.  With unparalleled engineering and breakthrough technology, NJRC has set the standards in quality, durability, and efficient VSAT products in the industry.
NJRC products are used globally across many satellite communications equipment including VSAT terminals, mobile communications, marine radomes, communications-on-the-move (COTM), aerospace, and military man-packs.  Engineers who knows the industry knows that NJRC is the name for top performance and long lasting equipment.









 











 


























 









Back to Top


























Leadership  










































 













 





Leadership




A Message from the CEO of Sojitz Corporation of America

Sojitz Corporation of America has remained successful for over 50 years by providing knowledge, speed, and networking to our trading and investment  business activities. We continue to expand and diversify our business model in the fast-paced and rapidly changing modern era.
Based in New York and on my second assignment in the United States, I am excited to  lead the expansion of business in such a dynamic region such as the Americas. Our guiding principles are to conduct business with trust, speed, and perseverance while innovating to take on new challenges. The long and close relationships we’ve built with business partners around the world are proof that these principles have stood the test of time. Sojitz’s greatest asset, our employees, adhere to these time-honored tenets while continually bringing “New Way, New Value” to the Americas region.


.
.






 











 


























 









